2:
You are the one who judges all people on the earth;
\q1 so arise and give them what they deserve.
\q1

4:
They do evil things, and they boast about doing them;
\q2 how long will they be allowed to continue doing that?
\q1

5:
Yahweh, it is as though those wicked people were crushing us, your people;
\q2 they oppress the nation that you have made and that belongs to you alone.
\q1

8:
You evil people who rule Israel, you are foolish and stupid;
\q2 when will you become wise?
\q1

9:
God made our ears;
\q2 do you think that he cannot hear what you say?
\q1 He created our eyes;
\q2 do you think that he cannot see the evil things that you do?
\q1

10:
He corrects the leaders of other nations;
\q2 do you think that he will not punish you?
\q1 He is the one who knows everything;
\q2 why do you think that he does not know what you do?
\q2

14:
Yahweh will not abandon his people;
\q2 he will not desert those who belong to him .
\q1

22:
But Yahweh has become like my fortress;
\q2 my God is like a huge rock on which I am protected.
\q1

23:
He will punish those wicked leaders in return for the things that they have done;
\q2 he will get rid of them because of the sins that they have committed;
\q2 yes, Yahweh our God will wipe them out.
